feat(ui): transition to light emerald theme and accessibility improvements

- Refactored the entire UI from a dark theme to a bright, "glassmorphism" light theme based on emerald, teal, and cyan palettes.
- Removed gray (slate) and yellow (amber) in favor of teal and cyan for better visual cohesion.
- Added ADHD-friendly reading styles to algorithm descriptions (soft contrast, larger text, relaxed line-height, and pastel backgrounds).
- Fixed `InputPanel` overflow bugs (e.g., String 1 & 2 in sequence alignment) by forcing 100% width and responsive truncation.
- Color-coded `Sidebar` syllabus modules for quicker navigation (Emerald, Cyan, Indigo, Rose).
- Added variable input logic and backtracking/highlights for Knapsack and Sequence Alignment in Dynamic Programming.
- Implemented automatic "dezoom" scaling for recursive trees and graph SVG canvases to prevent overflow clipping.
- Restructured layout logic, replacing CodePanel with ExecutionPanel and AnalysisPanel.
